-- Qualcomm posts higher profit, raises outlook
-- 
-- Wed Jul 25, 2007 4:24pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/07/25/us-qualcomm-results-idUSWEN967420070725

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Qualcomm Inc ( QCOM.O ) on Wednesday posted a higher quarterly profit and revenue rose on improving demand for its mobile phone chips and technology licenses. 

 Its shares rose 1.9 percent in after hours trade after closing at $42.45 on the Nasdaq as the company said it was increasing its earnings and revenue outlook for the year. Qualcomm's net profit rose to $798 million, or 47 cents share for its fiscal third quarter ended in June, from $643 million, or 37 cents a share in the year-ago quarter. Excluding its investment arm, Qualcomm said it earned 55 cents per share. Analysts on average had expected 51 cents per share, according to Reuters Estimates. Revenue rose to $2.33 billion from $1.95 billion a year ago and compared with analyst revenue estimates of $2.26 billion. Excluding its investment arm, Qualcomm forecast full-year 2007 earnings per share of $1.95 to $1.97 on revenue of $8.72 billion to $8.82 billion compared with its previous forecast for earnings per share of $1.57 to $1.61 per share on revenue of $8.4 billion to $8.7 billion. Analysts on average had expected revenue of $8.71 billion for the year, according to Reuters Estimates. The company forecast fiscal fourth-quarter net earnings per share of 41 cents to 43 cents on revenue of $2.15 billion to $2.25 billion. Excluding its investment arm, Qualcomm said it expects earnings per share of 48 cents to 50 cents per share. Analysts on average were expecting fourth-quarter earnings of 47 cents per share on revenue of $2.2 billion, according to Reuters Estimates. Qualcomm -- the main chip supplier for phones based on CDMA, the mostly widely used mobile phone technology in the United States -- faces several legal cases including a government ban on the U.S. sale of some phones that include its chips. (Reporting by  Sinead Carew )